HEADWORD: Eupeptic
<hw>Eu*pep"tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/.]</ety>
<def>Of or pertaining to good digestion; easy of digestion; having a
good digestion; <as>as, <ex>eupeptic</ex> food; an <ex>eupeptic</ex>
man.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Wrapt in lazy <qex>eupeptic</qex> fat.</q>
<rj><qau>Carlyle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

